@inherits ComponentBase

@* THE SHADOWING PAIR (decision 173, register C4). A sibling ComponentBase.razor sits beside this file.
   In real Blazor that sibling legally SHADOWS the framework base -- `@inherits ComponentBase` then
   resolves to the sibling component, not Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.ComponentBase. Filament must
   MERGE the sibling here, not treat the name as the default: the default fallback fires only AFTER the
   sibling-existence check fails, and here it succeeds. #out renders `currentCount`, declared in the
   sibling. If the C4 fallback wrongly fired, `currentCount` would be unresolved and this would refuse;
   it compiles, which is the proof the shadow is merged. *@

<div id="wrap"><span id="out">@currentCount</span></div>
